<TITLE> Bangladesh face hosts Malaysia on opening day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 7 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh will take on hosts Malaysia in one of two opening day matches of the Pestabola Merdeka Cup at the MBPJ Stadium in Kuala Lumpur on August 20. Bangladesh have been drawn in Group A along with Myanmar, Lesotho and hosts Malaysia in the eight-nation cup, the Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) confirmed Tuesday. The Group B comprises Singapore, Zimbabwe, Uganda and Indonesia. Bangladesh will play their second group match against Lesotho on August 22 and the last match against Myanmar on August 24. The group champions and runners-up of each group will qualify for the semifinals, scheduled to be played on August 27 before the final takes place on August 29 at the same venue. The BFF is yet to finalise which team would go to Malaysia as Bangladesh will also take part in Nehru Cup in India at the same time. Two teams of the BFF are gearing up for the tournaments at Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan under the guidance of India coach Syed Naeemuddin. 
